  <reviews>
    <item index="0">
      <text>Suffice it to say nothing about this pumped-up, hyperthyroidal Tony Scott revenge flick makes sense, but it takes two hours to kill off as many people and demolish as many vehicles as Charles Bronson used to do in 30 minutes.</text>
      <source>New York Observer</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.rotten</image>
      <link>http://www.nyobserver.com/pages/story.asp?ID=8975</link>
      <author>Rex Reed</author>
    </item>
    <item index="1">
      <text>Intentional or not, Man on Fire's over-the-top evocation of Christian retribution goes a long way to making this otherwise standard revenge fantasy watchable.</text>
      <source>Village Voice</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.villagevoice.com/issues/0417/ng.php</link>
      <author>David Ng</author>
    </item>
    <item index="2">
      <text>Long and torturous.</text>
      <source>Toronto Star</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.rotten</image>
      <link>http://WWW.TheStar.COM/NASApp/cs/ContentServer?pagename=thestar/Layout/Article_Type1&amp;c=Article&amp;cid=1082714684537&amp;call_pageid=1022183557980&amp;col=1022183560753</link>
      <author>Peter Howell</author>
    </item>
    <item index="3">
      <text>Overlong, off-putting and at times sadistic.</text>
      <source>Seattle Times</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.rotten</image>
      <link>http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?slug=man23&amp;date=20040423</link>
      <author>Moira MacDonald</author>
    </item>
    <item index="4">
      <text>This is garbage, but it's entertaining garbage.</text>
      <source>San Francisco Chronicle</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2004/04/23/DDG2068NVD1.DTL&amp;type=movies</link>
      <author>Mick LaSalle</author>
    </item>
    <item index="5">
      <text>If your idea of a bargain is two bad movies for the price of one, then shell out for Man on Fire.</text>
      <source>Globe and Mail</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.rotten</image>
      <link>http://www.globeandmail.com/servlet/ArticleNews/movie/MOVIEREVIEWS/20040423/FIRE23</link>
      <author>Rick Groen</author>
    </item>
    <item index="6">
      <text>Easily the best of the recent spate of cynical and violent revenge/vigilante dramas.</text>
      <source>Detroit Free Press</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://ae.freep.com/entertainment/ui/michigan/movie.html?id=135897&amp;reviewid=14926</link>
      <author>Terry Lawson</author>
    </item>
    <item index="7">
      <text>Punch drunk with sadism and sentimentality.</text>
      <source>Denver Post</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.rotten</image>
      <link>http://www.denverpost.com/Stories/0,1413,36~82~2099477,00.html</link>
      <author>Michael Booth</author>
    </item>
    <item index="8">
      <text>A highly watchable action thriller with one big flaw: It feels like two different movies aimed at two different audiences.</text>
      <source>CNN.com</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.fresh</image>
      <link>http://www.cnn.com/2004/SHOWBIZ/Movies/04/23/man.fire/index.html</link>
      <author>Paul Clinton (CNN.com)</author>
    </item>
    <item index="9">
      <text>Tony Scott's Man on Fire employs superb craftsmanship and a powerful Denzel Washington performance in an attempt to elevate genre material above its natural level, but it fails.</text>
      <source>Chicago Sun-Times</source>
      <image>rottentomatoes://image.review.rotten</image>
      <link>http://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/man-on-fire-2004</link>
      <author>Roger Ebert</author>
    </item>
  </reviews>
